Rating: 2
Quite disappointed in the outcome of this recipe. I used scallops, baby shrimp and fresh dungeness crab to make it more special. Sad to say there was so little flavor, even though I upped the amount of garlic. The confusing thing is the name of this recipe being "Scallop Gratins". A gratin is usually a topping mixture of breadcrumbs, cheese, and butter (or oil). However, this recipe has absolutely no cheese. That being said, I added about 1/3 cup of parmesan to the bread crumbs, which still didn't do a whole lot to improve this.

