Rating: 4
I don't know how anyone could make this dish bland. With a ratio of 3 Tbsp butter to about 4 Tbsp of seasonings, plus salt and pepper, you're pretty much guaranteed lots of flavor unless you leave some stuff out. I upped the garlic, because I love garlic, but it would have been just as good without the extra. Make sure you do add salt and fresh-ground black pepper. Anyway, I had a few scallops and a few shrimp, so I used both, and they were perfect after 20 minutes. I only have 8 oz. ramekins, so they were stuffed full, but the flavor was great and the juices good for dipping bread into. Make sure you don't skimp on the crumbs!

