Rating: 3
Yum! I made this as soon as I saw it in the 1/02 Bon Appetit. I do not like French bread, so I use crumbs I've made from bread left from a dinner--usually sourdough or a rosemary peasant bread (stored in zippered bags in the freezer). I watch it closely in the oven; it doesn't usually take the full time given.

Rating: 3
This was tasty and very easy, but the scallops were already overcooked after only 15 minutes; I hate to think how rubbery they would have been after the full 25 called for in the recipe. Also, the parsley in the butter mixture was drying out and starting to get black after 15 minutes. I suspect the whole thing would be perfect after only about ten minutes. Also, the 1-1/4 cup ramkins specified in the recipe were a bit too big for the job. I had to spread the scallops out, which may have contributed to the speed with which they cooked. I had been tempted to cheat and use prepared bread crumbs, but I am glad that I didn't, as the crumbs are a crucial element of this recipe.

